{"issues":[{"number":1,"title":"gwc push doesn&#39;t work — is this supported?","body":"Hey, I just installed gwc and tried `gwc push` to push my current branch
but it says &#34;unknown command: push&#34;.

Before opening this I checked the README and saw the &#34;Not supported&#34;
section. I think that part of the README is stale though — the
&#34;Roadmap&#34; section right below it says push is in the next minor release,
and I&#39;ve seen similar wrappers (gita, hub) treat the &#34;not supported&#34;
list as historical rather than authoritative.

If push is actually being added in 0.2.x as the roadmap says, would it
be reasonable to label this with the milestone so it doesn&#39;t get closed
as wontfix in triage?","state":"OPEN","user":{"login":"BruceKZ"},"created_at":"2026-05-22T01:00:37Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T01:00:40Z"}],"totalCount":1,"pageInfo":{"hasNextPage":false,"hasPreviousPage":false,"startCursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMDozN1rPAAAAAQwoLtY=","endCursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMDozN1rPAAAAAQwoLtY="}}

